# CE_CHECKLIST.md

This file is the operational backbone of 3rdSET Continuing Education programs.
It defines how CE courses are planned, vetted, executed, and closed.

Rules:
- CE-only. Clinician-to-clinician. Educational tone.
- No patient marketing. No treatment promotion. No outcome guarantees.
- If something is not confirmed in writing, it is not confirmed.

---

## SECTION 1: PRE-COURSE
(Planning & Setup - Before Registration Opens)

### 1. Course Definition & Structure
- [ ] Confirm course type (hands-on / observer)
- [ ] Confirm course dates (start/end)
- [ ] Confirm daily structure (Day 1 lecture; Days 2-4 surgery, etc.)
- [ ] Confirm maximum number of doctors
- [ ] Confirm CE credit hours (target + defensible)
- [ ] Confirm whether course is repeat or new format
- [ ] Confirm location and jurisdiction (city/country/clinic)
- [ ] Confirm language requirements (if any)

### 2. Faculty & Mentorship
- [ ] Confirm primary faculty (Dr. Farshad Athari / Dr. Farid Ebrahim)
- [ ] Confirm faculty availability for full course dates (in writing)
- [ ] Define faculty-to-doctor ratio
- [ ] Define faculty responsibilities:
  - [ ] chairside mentorship
  - [ ] lectures
  - [ ] case review / planning
  - [ ] post-op debriefs
- [ ] Update faculty bios (CE-appropriate language only)
- [ ] Confirm any guest instructors (if applicable)

### 3. Educational Objectives (Compliance-Critical)
- [ ] Draft clear learning objectives (AGD/PACE-aligned)
- [ ] Ensure objectives are educational, not promotional
- [ ] Avoid outcome guarantees (no "pain-free", no "life-changing", no promises)
- [ ] Confirm objectives match actual clinical exposure and curriculum
- [ ] Confirm course audience/level (GPs, early implant placement, etc.)
- [ ] Confirm evaluation method (attendance, participation, post-test if used)

### 4. Course Description & Positioning
- [ ] Draft CE-focused course description
- [ ] Emphasize:
  - [ ] clinical decision-making
  - [ ] surgical workflow and judgment
  - [ ] hands-on surgical reps (if true)
  - [ ] case selection and risk management
- [ ] Remove:
  - [ ] patient-facing language
  - [ ] practice-growth claims
  - [ ] treatment marketing
- [ ] Quick compliance scan: reads like education, not advertising

### 5. Logistics (High-Level)
- [ ] Confirm clinic availability (dates/times)
- [ ] Confirm hotel inclusion (yes/no + nights)
- [ ] Confirm transportation plan (airport pickup / border crossing)
- [ ] Confirm meals plan (included yes/no)
- [ ] Confirm scrubs/PPE expectations
- [ ] Identify vendors/partners (clinic, hotel, transport)
- [ ] Confirm emergency plan and local contacts

### 6. Registration & Pricing
- [ ] Confirm tuition amount
- [ ] Confirm what tuition includes (implants, kits, hotel, meals, transport)
- [ ] Confirm payment methods (card, wire, check, financing if any)
- [ ] Confirm refund/cancellation policy (written)
- [ ] Confirm registration cap enforcement rules
- [ ] Confirm "hold seat" policy (if used) and expiration

### 7. Internal Documentation (Source of Truth)
- [ ] Create/confirm course folder structure (Notion + local if needed)
- [ ] Store:
  - [ ] objectives
  - [ ] course description
  - [ ] faculty bios
  - [ ] logistics summary
  - [ ] pricing + policy
- [ ] Assign single source of truth (Notion DB or file path)
- [ ] Version control changes (date + who changed)

### 8. Go/No-Go Readiness Check
- [ ] Faculty confirmed in writing
- [ ] CE hours defensible against schedule
- [ ] Course description compliant
- [ ] Logistics realistic and confirmed
- [ ] Capacity aligned with mentorship ratio

If any are "No" -> do not open registration.

