## SECTION 2: DOCTOR INTAKE & VETTING
(Lead Handling - Qualification - Acceptance)

### 1. Intake Minimum Data (Required)
- [ ] Full name
- [ ] Email
- [ ] Cell
- [ ] Dental license number + state/country
- [ ] Practice name + city/state
- [ ] Specialty (GP/OS/Perio/Prosth, etc.)
- [ ] Years in practice (approx.)
- [ ] Course date they want

### 2. Fit & Readiness (Internal)
- [ ] Reason for taking course (what they want to improve)
- [ ] Current surgical comfort:
  - [ ] extractions (routine vs surgical)
  - [ ] flap/suture comfort
  - [ ] grafting exposure (none/basic/GBR)
- [ ] Implant exposure:
  - [ ] none / restoring only / placed before / placing now
- [ ] Expectations alignment:
  - [ ] understands this is intensive
  - [ ] understands this is hands-on surgical training (if true)
  - [ ] understands small group format and pace
- [ ] Red flags:
  - [ ] unrealistic promises requested
  - [ ] demands guaranteed implant count
  - [ ] patient marketing questions (redirect; do not engage)

### 3. Documentation to Collect (As Needed)
- [ ] License verification (if applicable)
- [ ] ID/passport info for travel (only when accepted)
- [ ] Dietary restrictions
- [ ] Dominant hand
- [ ] Scrub size

### 4. Acceptance Decision
- [ ] Accepted
- [ ] Waitlist
- [ ] Not a fit (politely close loop)

### 5. Acceptance Message (Operational)
- [ ] Send acceptance + next steps checklist:
  - [ ] invoice/payment link
  - [ ] travel window and pickup guidance
  - [ ] packing essentials (passport, scrubs, loupes if applicable)
  - [ ] required forms (if any)

### 6. CRM Hygiene (HubSpot/Notion)
- [ ] Create/Update doctor record
- [ ] Tag course date
- [ ] Track status: Lead -> Qualified -> Accepted -> Paid -> Confirmed -> Attended
- [ ] Log key notes (expectations, constraints, timing)

