## SECTION 5: LIVE COURSE EXECUTION
(Day 1 Lecture - Days 2-4 Surgery)

### 1. Day 1 (Lecture / Foundation)
- [ ] Attendance recorded
- [ ] Agenda followed (or changes noted)
- [ ] Objectives reviewed with group
- [ ] Safety / clinical protocols reviewed
- [ ] Dinner + schedule confirmation for next day

### 2. Surgery Days (Daily)
- [ ] Morning huddle: cases, roles, sequence
- [ ] Confirm consent/process requirements are met on-site
- [ ] Track each doctor participation:
  - [ ] cases assisted
  - [ ] implants placed (if tracked)
  - [ ] key learning points
- [ ] Daily debrief: complications, lessons, Q&A
- [ ] Capture internal notes for improvements

### 3. Professional Standards
- [ ] CE tone maintained (education-first)
- [ ] No patient advertising language in any materials
- [ ] No outcome guarantees stated

### 4. Documentation During Course
- [ ] Daily attendance log
- [ ] Any schedule deviations logged
- [ ] Any incidents documented internally

